Description.div: On the following pages you will be asked %System_NumberOfQuestions% questions about work health and safety law.

div.font: You will be asked multiple choice questions. Answer each question by clicking the button to the left of the most appropriate response.
After you answer the last question, you will be given the chance to review and then submit your answers.

Description.div: Please note that if you exit the quiz before clicking the Submit Answers button then your answers will not be saved.
To move between questions, use the ◄ and ► navigation buttons on the bottom right of the page.

strong.strong: What do good work health and safety practices achieve?

Answer.Description: Create an awareness of issues among employees
Help employees identify potential issues
Give employees the tools on how to respond if something goes wrong
All of the above

strong.strong: How can you ensure you are informed of WHS laws?

Answer.Description: Reading your employer's WHS policies and procedures
Regularly reading the policies and procedures that apply to your work
Speaking to your employer about changes you think should be made
All of the above

strong.strong: What is true in relation to workplace safety?

Answer.Description: Implementation of good policies guarantees workplace safety
Everyone within the workplace has an active role to play
Only employers can be charged with WHS offences
Minimising any health and safety risks to visitors is unimportant

strong.strong: What is NOT an objective of the WHS Act?

Answer.Description: Facilitate a segmented, state-by-state approach to work health and safety laws
Protect the health, safety and welfare of all persons from risks arising from the workplace
Facilitate advice, information sharing, education and training about work health and safety
Provide a framework for continuous improvements in work health and safety standards

strong.strong: What is a health and safety representative?

Answer.Description: A person appointed by the health and safety regulator in a jurisdiction
A union official who has the authority to enter a workplace
A person conducting a business or undertaking
A worker who represents a group of workers in WHS matters

strong.strong: Who bears the primary duty of care for work health and safety?

Answer.Description: WHS entry permit holders
Workers
PCBUs
Health and safety inspectors

strong.strong: What does the term reasonably practicable mean?

Answer.Description: A health and safety representative must do everything they can at all times to ensure the health and safety of others
A duty holder must, within reason, do what they can at a particular time to ensure the health and safety of others
A health and safety representative must do everything they can at a particular time to ensure his or her own health and safety
A duty holder must do everything they can at all times to ensure his or her own health and safety

strong.strong: A particular duty can only be imposed on one person. True or false?

Answer.Description: True
False

strong.strong: When can you contract out of a duty?

Answer.Description: By including a term to a contract that excludes, limits or modifies the relevant section of the WHS Act
By transferring a duty to another person
You can never contract out of a duty
When a person has more than one duty, they can choose to contract out of one if it is not reasonably practicable

strong.strong: Which parties have an obligation to consult with each other?

Answer.Description: People who owe duties in relation to different matters must consult, cooperate and coordinate with each other
People who owe duties in relation to the same matter must consult, cooperate and coordinate with each other
Health and safety inspectors must consult with WHS entry permit holders about work health and safety matters
PCBUs must consult with WHS entry permit holders about work health and safety matters

strong.strong: If a PCBU cannot resolve a WHS issue with his or her workers, what party may the regulator appoint?

Answer.Description: Fair Work Australia
An official negotiator
Health and safety inspector
None of the above

strong.strong: Complete the sentence. When consulting with workers, a PCBU is NOT required to…

Answer.Description: … take all actions recommended by the workers
… share relevant information
… take the workers’ views into account
… give workers a reasonable opportunity to express their views

strong.strong: Which is true about the duty to consult with others?

Answer.Description: If more than one person has a duty in respect of the same matter, each must consult with each other
There is no duty to consult with other duty holders, only with the PCBU
If people share a duty to the same matter, they must consult, cooperate and coordinate, so far as is reasonably practicable, with each other
Any individual who breaches this duty may face a maximum penalty of $200,000

strong.strong: Complete the sentence. To eliminate or minimise risks in the workplace, you can…

Answer.Description: … ignore any safety issues
… report any potential risks in the workplace
… leave it to management to identify risks
All of the above

strong.strong: What can you do to minimise risk in the workplace?

Answer.Description: Wait for your manager to make training available
Develop, but not implement, risk management strategies
Comply with any directions and safety information, and make sure others do too
Not attend a training session because you think you already know the material
